		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Can someone help me find a diagram for modding the Retron 1 (nes/clone), so I can play Castlevania 3 on it? I bought the &quot;Hex Inverter IC 7404&quot;, the picture below is an FC Twin diagram and not the Retron 1 board. I am including my guesses where the points would go but my confidence isn't their and would ask for confirmation and help.<br /><br />The wires go from 1, 2, 7, 14 on the Hex as shown here:<br /><br /><img src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-GCrPYE5P6zM/VVrXo6bkp3I/AAAAAAAACRI/ZS4whtui2rc/s1600/02.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><a href="http://14thlord.blogspot.com/2015/05/retrobit-project-castlevania-3.html" class="postlink">FC Twin</a><br /><br /><img src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-x9NOdmcRnYs/VVrePd1GeMI/AAAAAAAACR0/tsD4cXhcKsw/s1600/7400%2B1.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />So I gather from <a href="http://14thlord.blogspot.com/2015/06/internal-photos-of-retrobits-retro.html" class="postlink">images I found online</a> for the disassembling of the Retron 1 the solder points should be like this:<br /><br /><img src="http://i63.tinypic.com/2mmitn4.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Is this right??? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_question.gif" alt=":?:" title="Question" /> Also do the wires on the HEX #1, 2, go to the same solder point on the Retron 1 board #65? Thanks. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /><br /><br /><strong>Edit:</strong> Nvm the last question, I got it. 1Y (left) &amp; 1A (right). <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" />

		

